  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  From <fr:link href="/schm-LAYT/" title="Quasi-compactness is affine admissible" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LAYT/" display-uri="schm-LAYT" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-LAYT/" display-uri="schm-LAYT" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="/schm-3R68/" title="Closed immersions are affine admissible" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-3R68/" display-uri="schm-3R68" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-3R68/" display-uri="schm-3R68" /></fr:link>, via <fr:link href="/schm-AOI5/" title="Diagonalisation preserves affine admissibility" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-AOI5/" display-uri="schm-AOI5" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-AOI5/" display-uri="schm-AOI5" /></fr:link> we know that both <fr:link href="/schm-0B23/" title="Quasi-separated and separated morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-0B23/" display-uri="schm-0B23" type="local">quasi-separated and separated</fr:link> morphisms are <fr:link href="/schm-NAP1/" title="Affine admissible classes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-NAP1/" display-uri="schm-NAP1" type="local">affine admissble</fr:link>.
</html:p>
