                <fr:title text="Quasi-separated and separated schemes from morphisms">Quasi-separated and separated schemes from morphisms</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Remark</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  Note that a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-FEIP/" title="Quasi-separated schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FEIP/" display-uri="schm-FEIP" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link> iff <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \to  1]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/schm-0B23/" title="Quasi-separated and separated morphisms" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-0B23/" display-uri="schm-0B23" type="local">quasi-separated</fr:link>, since the diagonal <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \to  X \times  X]]></fr:tex> is quasi-compact iff the intersection of quasi-compact opens in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is again quasi-compact. Hence, we also say <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is <html:em>separated</html:em> if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X \to  1]]></fr:tex> is separated.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
