          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
  If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D \to  E]]></fr:tex> makes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex> a <fr:link href="/idem-comm-7K36/" title="Relative Boolean algebra" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-7K36/" display-uri="idem-comm-7K36" type="local"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>-Boolean algebra</fr:link>, then so is the pushout <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \to  A \otimes _D E]]></fr:tex> for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D \to  A]]></fr:tex>. This follows from the characterisation in <fr:link href="/schm-FHDX/" title="Separated morphisms between affine schemes" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FHDX/" display-uri="schm-FHDX" type="local">Proposition <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-FHDX/" display-uri="schm-FHDX" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="/schm-S4EV/" title="Quasi-separated and separated maps are affine admissible" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-S4EV/" display-uri="schm-S4EV" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-S4EV/" display-uri="schm-S4EV" /></fr:link>.
